To automate selecting all checkboxes on a page and then save them with a click of a button, you can use JavaScript along with event listeners. Here’s a concise way to do it:

1. **Select all checkboxes** using `document.querySelectorAll`.
2. **Loop through them** and check each one.
3. **Add an event listener** to the "Save" button to trigger the checkbox selection.

Here's a simple example:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Checkbox Automator</title>
</head>
<body>
    <input type="checkbox" name="chk1"> Checkbox 1<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="chk2"> Checkbox 2<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="chk3"> Checkbox 3<br>

    <button id="saveButton">Save</button>

    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
            const checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]');
            const saveButton = document.getElementById('saveButton');

            // Function to select all checkboxes
            function selectAllCheckboxes() {
                checkboxes.forEach(checkbox => checkbox.checked = true);
            }

            // Add event listener to save button
            saveButton.addEventListener('click', selectAllCheckboxes);
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This code will automatically select all checkboxes when the "Save" button is clicked. Adjust the selector or logic as needed for your specific use case!

